 The 1969 Dixie 500 is a NASCAR Grand National Series racing event that took place on August 10, 1969 at Atlanta International Raceway in Hampton, Georgia, U.S. After 334 laps (3 hours of racing), LeeRoy Yarbrough defeated David Pearson by 5 seconds in front of a live audience of 14300 people.[1] The pole position winner was Cale Yarborough who drove at speeds up to 155.413 miles per hour (250.113km/h) prior to the race.[1] John Sears had a problem with his engine and had to withdraw from the race on the third lap.[1] All 40 competitors on the racing grid were born in the United States of America; no foreigners attempted to qualify.[1] Nord Krauskopf's entry (with Bobby Isaac as the driver) finished in 34th place.[1] Ford vehicles managed to dominate the starting grid.[1] The winner of the race received $18,620 of the total winners while the last-place finisher went home with a meager $725.[2]
